            <abstract>
                <p>Story about a child that was thrown into the sea by an evil rich man, saved by <persName ref="PRS7049Michael"/> and 
                    found by a shepherd, who named him <persName ref="PRS11321Talafinos">ተላሶን፡ </persName>. The story is a variation 
                    of <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3959Homily"/> and <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1295Dersan#CommemorativeTemple"/>. Often defined as nagar, but also frequently as dǝrsān in some 
                    other manuscripts. Usually attributed either to the month Ḥamle or to Miyāzyā but in <ref type="mss" corresp="BMLacq776"/>
                    in connection with the month of Maggābit. Usually attributed to <persName ref="PRS10425Yohanne"/></p>
            </abstract>
